Ricky Gervais is gonna be on the Daily Show tomorrow!!!  Holy FUCK!!!

For you uncultured motherfuckers out there...

Ricky Gervais starred on the original "The Office" (the good one... that's also British).

Watch it.  Dammit.

So, not much is going on in my life, at the moment.  Just school, mostly.

But here's an update on minor happenings:

My new cell phone is AWESOME.  Icarus makes a kick-ass background.

I got lunch today with a few friends (Sam - from Santa Cruz High, Jennica - from Santa Cruz High and also a friend of Jeff's, and Chris - from my Philosophy of Mind class).

I've been playing Kingdom of Loathing.  It's pretty fun.  If anyone plays, look me up.  My screen name is Skryt.

I'm awfully happy about Emma moving into her dorm.  She's adorable, and she appears to be quite quite happy with it all.  She's in Porter College.  And gorgeous.

School is uneventful at best.

I guess that's it...

I totally am importing songs from iPod onto my computer.  I'll have most of them back in an hour or so (I have A LOT of songs).

I went all over the county looking for cell phones, but with no avail.  Fuckers.

I shall order them online!

Oldboy is a REALLY good movie, by the way.

I accidentally deleted all of my music.

I'm going to mess around with some programs and my iPod so I can, like, TOTALLY try to get most of it back.

Damn...

Spending the night with Emma at Kathleen's house.

WHOO!

Over 90 pages this week...

So, as some of you may expect from the subject, today was a good day.

My classes are all great, so far.  I'll be finding out about Psychology of Women tomorrow.  Man, that's a 2 hour and 50 minute class... fun.

Anyways, I hung out with Andy and Justin for a bit.  We got lunch at Noah's.  Much fun.

Also, Emma will be over in a bit.

I guess that's it...

OH!  Wait!  I got a pair of SEXY jeans from the GAP.  Y'know that whole iTunes free song offer for just trying a pair on?  Yeah.  Once you try them on, you don't want to take them off.  I wore them today, and they were HEAVENLY.  Fuckin' HEAVENLY, man!

AAAAnyways...
The bus strike has been moved to September 8th.

Dudes!

Okay, so, there's TOTALLY gonna be that whole thing where telemarketers can call your cell phone in 25 days from now.

So, to sign up for the whole "do not call" list, here's what ya do:

You can call 1-888-382-1222 from your cell phone that you wanna protect.  It's pretty easy, being automated and all.  You just have to choose your preferred language, choose to register your phone, and then enter your number with the area code.

You can also go to http://www.donotcall.gov.

I did the automated phone dealy, myself.

AAAAnways... yeah...

Cabrillo starts tomorrow.

After many happenings, I will no longer have the two classes I was excited about, which were Sign Language and Ethics.  Their replacements, respectively, are Philosophy of Mind and Psychology of women.

I lack interest in my entire semester.

Although, there is good news.  I discovered that I had 9.5 credits that I completely forgot about from my days of homeschooling and SCHS.

It doesn't help me fulfill requirements other than pure credits, however.

I bought the starter set of and a booster pack for the D&D Miniatures game.  It's fairly cool, although I don't have the patience to read the rather long instruction booklet though.

Emma is in San Francisco for now.  She's babysitting her cousins, or something.  I miss and love her so damn much.

I'm considering a new tattoo, which is from 28 Days Later.  It's scrawled on the wall inside of a church towards the beginning of the movie:

REPENT
THE END IS
EXTREMELY
FUCKING
NIGH

Torrey is coming to SC in a few days.  It's rather exciting.  I look forward to seeing him.

I'm going to see Corpse Bride with Amber and her boyfriend, Teddy.  That should be fun.

I need to spend my $50 GAP giftcard... hmm... what to get, what to get...

Rant rant rant rant rant... I'm sounding like Andy (I got dinner with him tonight).  Fuck.

Well, that's all that's happening with me.

Whoo.

Emma:

Happy approaching 9-thing!!!

Get better soon, dammit.

I love you lots.

-Totally me.
